<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-30-0313 </DOCNO><TEXT>This door has a membrane seal whose sealing strip rests against the chamberframe by means of contact pressure elements that are fixed to the bodyof the door, each contact pressure element consisting of a casing inwhich there is an adjustable spring and of a contact block against whichthe casing presses. The body of the door has integrally cast cams alongits periphery, said cams having rough cast traversing holes into whichthreaded bolts are set and screwed. Two or more threaded bolts pass througha crosspiece by which they are interconnected and to which are fixedthe casings of one or several contact pressure elements.</TEXT></DOC>